---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'how-it-works', text: 'How Evacuation Works', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'types', text: 'Types of Evacuation', level: 2 },
  { id: 'when-needed', text: 'When Evacuation Applies', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Adventure Sports Insurance', href: '/best/adventure-sports-insurance' },
  { title: 'Multi-Country Insurance', href: '/best/multi-country-insurance' },
  { title: 'Premium Insurance', href: '/best/premium-insurance' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Understanding Evacuation', href: '/guides/understanding-evacuation' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'limit', header: 'Evacuation Limit' },
  { key: 'repatriation', header: 'Repatriation' },
  { key: 'security', header: 'Security Evac' },
  { key: 'coordinates', header: 'Coordination' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', limit: 'Unlimited', repatriation: 'Included', security: 'Add-on', coordinates: 'Full service' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', limit: 'Unlimited', repatriation: 'Included', security: 'Add-on', coordinates: 'Full service' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', limit: '$500,000', repatriation: 'Included', security: 'Limited', coordinates: 'Good' },
  { provider: 'SafetyWing', limit: '$100,000', repatriation: 'Included', security: 'Not included', coordinates: 'Basic' },
  { provider: 'World Nomads', limit: '$500,000', repatriation: 'Included', security: 'Not included', coordinates: 'Good' },
];

const typesColumns = [
  { key: 'type', header: 'Evacuation Type' },
  { key: 'covers', header: 'What It Covers' },
  { key: 'typical', header: 'Typical Scenario' },
];

const typesRows = [
  { type: 'Medical evacuation', covers: 'Transport to adequate medical facility', typical: 'Remote area injury, local hospital inadequate' },
  { type: 'Medical repatriation', covers: 'Return to home country for treatment', typical: 'Long-term treatment needed in familiar system' },
  { type: 'Repatriation of remains', covers: 'Return of body in case of death', typical: 'Death abroad, family wants burial at home' },
  { type: 'Security evacuation', covers: 'Evacuation due to political/civil unrest', typical: 'War, coup, civil disturbance' },
  { type: 'Compassionate evacuation', covers: 'Family member transport', typical: 'Parent with sick child, family emergency' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Expat Insurance with Emergency Evacuation 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance with comprehensive medical evacuation and repatriation coverage. Find plans that get you home or to proper care when emergencies strike."
  headline="Best Expat Insurance with Emergency Evacuation"
  subheadline="When local hospitals can't treat you, evacuation coverage gets you to proper care—or home. Here are the best options for comprehensive evacuation protection."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-emergency-evacuation-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for Evacuation Coverage</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers offer the strongest emergency evacuation coverage:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🚁</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Overall Evacuation</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Unlimited evacuation coverage with full coordination services. Gets you to the right care anywhere in the world.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌐</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Network for Evacuation</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Unlimited evacuation with excellent global coordination. Strong hospital network at evacuation destinations.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💰</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Value Evacuation</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">IMG Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">$500,000 evacuation coverage at moderate prices. Good coordination and repatriation included.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🎒</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Budget Evacuation</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">SafetyWing</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">$100,000 evacuation at $45/month. Covers most scenarios for budget-conscious expats.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="how-it-works">How Emergency Evacuation Works</h2>
  <p>
    Emergency evacuation coverage kicks in when local medical care is inadequate:
  </p>

  <h3>The Process</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Emergency occurs:</strong> You need care that isn't available locally</li>
    <li><strong>Contact insurer:</strong> Call the emergency line (usually 24/7)</li>
    <li><strong>Assessment:</strong> Medical team determines if evacuation is necessary</li>
    <li><strong>Coordination:</strong> Insurer arranges transport, receiving hospital, etc.</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> You're transported to adequate medical facility</li>
    <li><strong>Treatment:</strong> Covered under your main medical benefits</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>What's Typically Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Air ambulance or medical flight</li>
    <li>Medical escort when needed</li>
    <li>Ground transport to/from airports</li>
    <li>Coordination and logistics</li>
    <li>Communication with family</li>
    <li>Sometimes accompanying family member travel</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>What's Not Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Evacuation when local care is adequate</li>
    <li>Non-emergency transport preferences</li>
    <li>Evacuation for pre-existing conditions (usually)</li>
    <li>Self-arranged evacuations without authorization</li>
    <li>Security evacuation (unless included)</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Evacuation Coverage"
    description="Compare plans with comprehensive emergency evacuation."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Evacuation Coverage Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Best Overall Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers unlimited emergency evacuation with comprehensive coordination services.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Unlimited evacuation coverage</li>
    <li>Full coordination—they handle everything</li>
    <li>24/7 emergency response team</li>
    <li>Medical escort included when needed</li>
    <li>Repatriation to home country included</li>
    <li>Family member travel coordination</li>
    <li>Global network of hospitals for destination</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing. Security evacuation is add-on. Best value if you also need comprehensive medical coverage.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best Network for Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global combines unlimited evacuation with an excellent hospital network worldwide.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Unlimited evacuation coverage</li>
    <li>Extensive global hospital network</li>
    <li>Direct billing at destination hospitals</li>
    <li>24/7 coordination team</li>
    <li>Medical repatriation included</li>
    <li>Family notification and support</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing. Security evacuation separate. Network strength varies by region.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>IMG Global — Best Value Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    IMG Global offers strong evacuation coverage at more moderate prices.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>$500,000 evacuation coverage</li>
    <li>More affordable than premium insurers</li>
    <li>Good coordination services</li>
    <li>Repatriation included</li>
    <li>Works well for most scenarios</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Not unlimited—$500,000 cap. Coordination may be slower. Limited security evacuation. Service level below premium insurers.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/img-global">Read our full IMG Global review</a></p>

  <h3>SafetyWing — Best Budget Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing includes $100,000 evacuation coverage even at their low price point.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>$100,000 evacuation included</li>
    <li>Only $45/month total</li>
    <li>Covers most realistic scenarios</li>
    <li>Repatriation included</li>
    <li>Easy to purchase</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Lower limit than full health plans. Basic coordination. No security evacuation. Travel medical only—not full health insurance.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/safetywing">Read our full SafetyWing review</a></p>

  <h2 id="types">Types of Evacuation Coverage</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={typesColumns} rows={typesRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Medical Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    The core evacuation benefit:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Transport to nearest adequate medical facility</li>
    <li>May be within country or international</li>
    <li>Decision based on medical necessity</li>
    <li>Includes air ambulance when needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Medical Repatriation</h3>
  <p>
    Getting you home for treatment:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Return to home country when medically stable</li>
    <li>For ongoing treatment in familiar system</li>
    <li>May include medical escort</li>
    <li>Usually included in evacuation coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Security Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    For political/civil emergencies:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Evacuation due to war, coup, civil unrest</li>
    <li>Usually a separate add-on benefit</li>
    <li>Not included in standard medical coverage</li>
    <li>Important for unstable regions</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Need Security Evacuation?"
    description="Some regions require additional security coverage."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="when-needed">When Evacuation Coverage Applies</h2>

  <h3>Evacuation Triggered When:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Local hospital cannot provide necessary treatment</li>
    <li>Required specialists not available locally</li>
    <li>Medical equipment/facilities inadequate</li>
    <li>Remote location with no nearby care</li>
    <li>Insurer's medical team approves evacuation</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Evacuation NOT Triggered When:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Local care is adequate (even if not preferred)</li>
    <li>You simply prefer treatment elsewhere</li>
    <li>Non-emergency situations</li>
    <li>Self-arranged without insurer approval</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions (usually)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Real Cost of Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    Why this coverage matters:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Air ambulance:</strong> $20,000-150,000+</li>
    <li><strong>Medical flight (commercial with escort):</strong> $10,000-50,000</li>
    <li><strong>Helicopter rescue:</strong> $5,000-30,000</li>
    <li><strong>International repatriation:</strong> $10,000-100,000+</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Without coverage, you pay these costs out-of-pocket or don't get evacuated.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>How much evacuation coverage do I need?</h3>
  <p>
    $100,000 covers most scenarios—even expensive air ambulances rarely exceed this. $500,000 or unlimited provides extra security for complex situations. Choose based on where you travel and your risk tolerance.
  </p>

  <h3>Who decides if I need evacuation?</h3>
  <p>
    The insurer's medical team makes this decision based on local medical capabilities and your condition. They coordinate with local doctors. You can't simply demand evacuation—it must be medically justified.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I be evacuated to any country I choose?</h3>
  <p>
    Not always. Evacuation is typically to the nearest adequate facility, not necessarily your home country. Repatriation to your home country usually happens once you're stable enough for non-emergency transport.
  </p>

  <h3>What about mountain rescue or sea rescue?</h3>
  <p>
    Search and rescue (SAR) is different from medical evacuation. Some adventure-focused plans include SAR; others don't. If you do adventure activities, verify SAR is covered. Mountain rescue helicopters can cost $10,000-30,000.
  </p>

  <h3>Does evacuation cover family members coming to me?</h3>
  <p>
    Some plans include coverage for a family member to travel to you in case of serious illness/injury. Others cover family member transport during evacuation. Check your specific plan benefits.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I arrange my own evacuation?</h3>
  <p>
    You may not be reimbursed. Insurers typically require that evacuations be coordinated through them so they can verify medical necessity and arrange appropriate transport. Self-arranged evacuations risk non-payment.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Evacuation coverage terms and limits vary by plan. We are not insurance brokers. Always verify current coverage directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
